Drivers, with 210 km/ h and hot drink between the legs gerast, gets GBP 1,000 penalty
A motorist was imposed a penalty in the amount of GBP 1,000, because it was up to 210 km/ h, and a hot drink between his legs.
Andrew Howie, 35, from Tiptree, Essex, on May 27, with his Mercedes-Benz on the A 120 in Braintree.
After the police stopped him, they discovered the beverage cup between his legs.
Before the Amtsgericht Colchester pled guilty Howie, driving without due care and attention.
He received seven points and a six-month ban.
Howie was also sentenced to pay costs of GBP 90 and a victim surcharge of GBP 100.
